    "id": "KIRA_CH1_KINGS_ROAD",
    "character": "KIRA",
    "description": "The King's Road stretches ahead, mud churned by centuries of carts and cavalry. You walk in disguise\u2014a peasant girl, dirt on your face, calluses faked on your hands.\n\nYour fingers itch with the urge to reach for the void. Eight years of hiding your nature. The magic sits coiled in your chest like a sleeping serpent, waiting.\n\nNear Millbrook, you smell the caravan before you see it: horse sweat, rope, the copper tang of fear.\n\nThree bandits have cornered a merchant wagon against a ditch. The merchant pleads\u2014something about his daughter, his wife.\n\nThe void whispers to you.",
