        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "KIRA_ENDING_MARTYR": {
    "id": "KIRA_ENDING_MARTYR",
    "character": "KIRA",
    "description": "You destroy the crown. All seven pieces shatter at once, releasing the Void Beast\u2014and you along with it.\n\nIn your final moment, you see the world freed. The Hollow King screams as he's unmade. Your mother feels peace for the first time in eight years.\n\nAnd you? You become part of the void\u2014not trapped, but free. A new guardian, watching over the world you saved.\n\nThe crown is gone. The Beast is gone. And in the silence of the void, you finally rest.",
    "ending": "MARTYR",
    "choices": []
  },
  "KIRA_ENDING_UNDYING": {
    "id": "KIRA_ENDING_UNDYING",
    "character": "KIRA",
    "description": "You claim the crown. Power floods through you\u2014unimaginable, terrifying, beautiful.\n\nYou are Aethon's heir now. The Undying. A god of the void.\n\nThe Hollow King cowers before you. You could destroy him\u2014or you could use him.\n\nYour mother looks at you with fear in her eyes. You've become something else. Something beyond human.\n\nThe world will never be the same. And neither will you.",
    "ending": "UNDYING",
    "choices": []
  },
  "KIRA_ENDING_HOLLOW": {
    "id": "KIRA_ENDING_HOLLOW",
    "character": "KIRA",
    "description": "You give yourself to the Hollow King. In exchange, your mother lives\u2014a mortal again, free at last.\n\nBut you? You're lost. Part of the darkness forever. A new prisoner in the void.\n\nSometimes, in her dreams, your mother feels you there. Reaching. Wanting. Never quite gone.\n\nAnd the crown remains, waiting for the next Nightwind to make the same choice.",
    "ending": "FOLLOW",
    "choices": []
  },
  "THERON_CH1_TAVERN": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_TAVERN",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "The Broken Blade tavern reeks of stale ale and desperation. You sit in the corner, a mug of something cheap and bitter in your weathered hands. Once, men knelt before you. Once, you wore the Silver Crown of the King's Guard. Now, you wear rags and a beard grown from neglect.\n\nThe fire crackles. Other patrons avoid your table\u2014they've heard the stories of Theron Ashford, the knight who failed his kingdom. The knight who couldn't save the king. The knight who chose survival over honor.\n\nYou drink to forget. But the void never lets you forget. It whispers in your dreams, in thebottom of your cup, in the eyes of every noble you've learned to hate.\n\nThe tavern door creaks open. A woman enters, cloaked in midnight blue. Her eyes find you immediately.\n\n'Theron Ashford,' she says. 'I've been looking for you.'",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Ignore her\u2014another creditor or bounty hunter",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_IGNORE",
        "effects": {
