  "THERON_CH1_IGNORE": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_IGNORE",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You don't look up. Can't she see you're busy drowning your sorrows? The void stirs in your chest\u2014that familiar ache of power you no longer deserve.\n\nShe sits across from you anyway. Her hand removes her hood, revealing silver-streaked hair and a face carved by decades of court intrigue. This is no ordinary hunter.\n\n'I am Lady Morgana Vance,' she says. 'High Advisor to Queen Seraphina. And I've come to offer you something precious: redemption.'\n\nThe word hits like a blade. Redemption. You almost laugh.\n\n'Your queen's guard killed my honor,' you say. 'Your queen's throne is built on lies.'\n\nMorgana smiles coldly. 'Then help me unbuild it. There's a Cult that operates in her name. The Ashfield Cult. And they need to be stopped.'",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Accept the mission\u2014finally, action",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "combat": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Demand payment first\u2014you need coin",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_PAYMENT",
        "effects": {
          "gold": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Ask for time to think\u2014too many scars",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_HESITATE",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_DEMAND": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_DEMAND",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "Your hand moves to your belt\u2014where your sword used to hang. You sold it three months ago for drink money. But the reflex remains.\n\nThe woman's eyes flick to your movement, then back to your face. No fear. Interesting.\n\n'I am Lady Morgana Vance,' she says. 'High Advisor to Queen Seraphina. And I don't have time for your posturing, Theron. Your king is dead. Your order is scattered. And your drinking won't bring them back.'\n\nThe words cut deeper than any blade. You could kill her. No\u2014you could never. But the rage is familiar. Better than the emptiness.\n\n'What do you want?' you growl.\n\nShe slides a parchment across the table. 'The Ashfield Cult. They've infiltrated the court. I need a hunter, not a knight. Someone who understands darkness.'\n\nHer eyes meet yours. 'Someone like you.'",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Take the contract\u2014let's end this",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "strength": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Negotiate terms\u2014nothing free in this world",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_PAYMENT",
        "effects": {
          "charisma": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "She's lying\u2014investigate first",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_SUSPICION",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_DECLINE": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_DECLINE",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You shake your head, not even looking at her. 'I'm retired. Find another broken knight to do your bidding.'\n\nBut she doesn't leave. Instead, she sits uninvited, her presence filling the space like a storm cloud.\n\n'Your princess died in that fire, Theron.'\n\nThe room goes silent. The void inside you roars.\n\n'Princess Elara. Trapped in the burning palace while you escaped. The king ordered you to save her, and you chose yourself.'\n\nYour hand shakes around the mug. 'I tried\u2014'\n\n'You tried to save yourself. The princess burned. And the Cult that set that fire? They're still out there. Worshipping false gods. Building power in the shadows.'\n\nShe leans close. 'Don't you want to know why?'\n\nThe question hangs in the air. And for the first time in years, you feel something other than emptiness. You feel hate.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Accept\u2014for her sake, for Elara",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "honor": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Who is she really?\u2014dig for truth",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_SUSPICION",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Walk away\u2014some debts can't be paid",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_LEAVE",
        "effects": {
          "humanity": -1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_MISSION": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You stand\u2014your knees aching, your back sore from years of hunched drinking. But for the first time, something feels right.\n\n'\u544a\u8bc9\u6211,' you say. 'Everything.'\n\nMorgana outlines the mission: The Ashfield Cult worships the Void\u2014that ancient nothing that existed before creation. They've been secretly sacrificing nobles, stealing artifacts, building toward something called the Convergence.\n\n'Vespera,' Morgana says. 'Their leader. Once a priestess of the light, now something else. She holds court in the old temple outside Thornwick.'\n\nShe hands you a purse\u2014heavy with gold. 'Find them. Expose them. And if you can... bring me proof of their conspiracy.'\n\nYou take the gold. You take the name. And you take the first step toward either redemption or ruin.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Travel directly to Thornwick\u2014confront them",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_JOURNEY",
        "effects": {
          "strength": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Gather intel first\u2014find allies",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_ALLIES",
        "effects": {
          "charisma": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Research the Cult\u2014understand the enemy",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_RESEARCH",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_PAYMENT": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_PAYMENT",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You hold out your hand. 'Gold. Fifty sovereigns. Upfront.'\n\nMorgana raises an eyebrow. 'You were once a knight of the realm. Now you bargain like a mercenary?'\n\n'I was a knight of a dead king. Now I'm just a man who needs drink money.'\n\nShe reaches into her cloak and produces a pouch. It clinks with more than fifty coins.\n\n'Seventy,' she says. 'But this comes with strings. I need the Cult exposed\u2014not just destroyed. Evidence that will convince the court. The queen's council is compromised, Theron. I need proof, not bodies.'\n\nYou weigh the pouch. Seventy sovereigns. Enough to drink yourself to death twice over.\n\n'Or,' she adds, 'I could simply leave. Find another broken knight. There's always more.'\n\nThe challenge hangs in the air. You take the gold.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Accept\u2014alliance sealed",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "gold": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Demand more\u2014your skills are valuable",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_DEMAND",
        "effects": {
          "charisma": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Accept but with conditions\u2014you won't kill innocents",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "honor": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_HESITATE": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_HESITATE",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You don't answer. Can't she see the scars? The memories? Every time you close your eyes, you see the flames. The princess screaming your name. The king's body, broken and burned.\n\n'I'll be here tomorrow,' Morgana says. 'And the day after. The Cult won't wait forever. Neither will I.'\n\nShe leaves a card on the table\u2014an address in the lower city. Then she's gone, swallowed by the night.\n\nYou stare at the card for hours. Redemption. Such a small word for such an enormous lie.\n\nBut dawn finds you outside that address. Old habits die hard. Duty, even when it's murdered, sometimes leaves a pulse.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Meet her at dawn\u2014you've made your choice",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "honor": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Still uncertain\u2014wait one more day",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_DELAY",
        "effects": {
          "humanity": -1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Prepare anyway\u2014equipment and supplies",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_PREPARE",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_CH1_SUSPICION": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_SUSPICION",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You hold her gaze. 'Why me? Any knight could do this. Any spy. Any assassin.'\n\nMorgana's smile is thin. 'Because any of them might be bought. The Cult has gold, Theron. More gold than the crown itself. But you?'\n\nShe leans back. 'You have nothing left to buy. And everything to prove.'\n\nThat stings. But it's also true.\n\n'I'll check your story,' you say. 'If you're lying, I'll find out.'\n\nShe nods. 'I would expect nothing less. The Ashfield Cult meets in the old temple at Thornwick. Their leader goes by Vespera. That's all I know\u2014and all I need you to discover.'\n\nShe stands to leave. 'I'll be in touch.'\n\nBut as the door closes, you notice something: her signet ring. It bears a symbol\u2014a crescent moon, intertwined with shadows. The symbol of the old priesthood.\n\nThe same symbol, you realize, that's been carved into the bodies of the Cult's victims.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Confront her about the symbol",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_CONFRONT",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Play along\u2014 gather evidence first",
        "leads_to": "THERON_CH1_MISSION",
        "effects": {
          "stealth": 1
        },
