  "THERON_CH1_PREPARE": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_PREPARE",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You spend the night preparing\u2014not for redemption, but for war. A sword from a dead guard. A dagger hidden in your boot. Bread and dried meat for the road.\n\nThe void responds to your preparation. It whispers of weaknesses, of angles of attack, of where to strike. You'd forgotten how much you knew.\n\nIn the morning, you feel almost human. Almost ready.\n\nBut Morgana isn't at her address. Instead, a messenger waits with a note: 'Temple of the Ash. Midnight. Come alone.'\n\nThe Temple of the Ash is a ruin\u2014a burnt-out church from the old king's time. No one goes there. No one remembers why.\n\nExcept you do. That's where the fire started. That's where the Cult made their first sacrifice.",
