  "THERON_CH1_TRAP": {
    "id": "THERON_CH1_TRAP",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You set a trap\u2014a false trail leading to an abandoned mill. Cultists will follow, thinking you isolated. Instead, they'll walk into a killzone.\n\nIt takes hours to prepare, but the void helps. It always helps when death is involved.\n\nThree Cultists take the bait. They're careless, expecting an easy target. They find you instead.\n\nThe fight is short. Your blade takes the first through the throat. The second falls to your counter. The third tries to run\u2014you let him go, so he'll bring others.\n\nBut something feels wrong. The Cultists are too weak, too poorly trained. They fight like fanatics, not soldiers.\n\nA noise behind you. You spin\u2014but it's already too late. A blade pierces your side.\n\nVespera steps from the shadows. She's beautiful, in a terrible way. Her eyes hold the void itself.\n\n'Theron Ashford,' she says. 'I've been waiting for you.'",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Fight her\u2014your death or hers",
