  "THERON_CH2_HEALER": {
    "id": "THERON_CH2_HEALER",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "A healer lives in the hills\u2014an old woman who remembers the old kingdom. She tends your wounds in silence, her hands glowing with light magic.\n\n'You carry the void,' she says. It's not a question.\n\nYou don't deny it. 'It won't let me die. I've tried.'\n\nShe laughs\u2014a dry, humorless sound. 'It won't let you live either. It's waiting, Theron. Feeding on your pain. The day you stop suffering is the day it consumes you.'\n\nShe speaks of a solution: The Temple of Ash holds the only seal strong enough to contain the void permanently. An ancient binding, placed during the Sundering.\n\n'But it's a prison,' she warns. 'Once you enter, you cannot leave. The void will be sealed inside you forever.'\n\nIs that death? Or is it peace?",
    "choices": [
