        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Find purpose\u2014become a protector",
        "leads_to": "THERON_ENDING_COMMANDER",
        "effects": {
          "charisma": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Fade away\u2014the void is patient",
        "leads_to": "THERON_ENDING_HOLLOW",
        "effects": {
          "humanity": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "THERON_ENDING_REDEEMED": {
    "id": "THERON_ENDING_REDEEMED",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You sacrifice yourself to save the world. It's the only noble thing you've ever done.\n\nThe void consumes you\u2014or perhaps you become it. Either way, the Beast is sealed. The Cult is destroyed. The children are saved.\n\nIn the final moment, you see Princess Elara\u2014not the monster she became, but the child she was. She's reaching for you. And this time, you reach back.\n\n'Thank you,' she whispers. 'For not giving up on me.'\n\nYou smile. 'I never gave up on myself. I just didn't know it yet.'\n\nThe darkness takes you. But it's not empty. It's not suffering. It's rest.\n\nThe kingdom calls you a hero. They build statues. They write songs. But you don't hear them. You're beyond their praise, beyond their blame.\n\nIn the void, you watch. And wait. And protect.\n\nPerhaps one day, you'll be called again. And perhaps next time, you'll be ready.",
    "ending": "REDEEMED",
    "choices": []
  },
  "THERON_ENDING_COMMANDER": {
    "id": "THERON_ENDING_COMMANDER",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You claim power. It's what you've always been, perhaps\u2014the monster in the shadows, waiting to be unleashed.\n\nWith the void at your command, you become something more than a knight. You become a ruler. The kingdom kneelsto you\u2014not because they want to, but because they have no choice.\n\nThe Cult is scattered. The Circle is broken. The court is your tool. And you sit upon the throne, looking down at a world that fears you.\n\nIs this redemption? No. It's something else. Something darker.\n\nBut you rule with a firm hand. No chaos. No Cults. No dangerous magic. The kingdom is safe\u2014so safe it chills.\n\nAnd sometimes, late at night, when you're alone in the throne room, you feel the void moving. It wants more. It always wants more.\n\nPerhaps one day, you'll lose yourself entirely. Become the very thing you fought. But not today.\n\nToday, you rule. And that's enough.",
    "ending": "COMMANDER",
    "choices": []
  },
  "THERON_ENDING_HOLLOW": {
    "id": "THERON_ENDING_HOLLOW",
    "character": "THERON",
    "description": "You survive. That's all. You always said you would.\n\nThe world burns around you. The Cult rises. The Circle falls. The kingdom descends into chaos. And you walk away, leaving nothing but footprints in the ash.\n\nThe void lives inside you\u2014patient, hungry, waiting. You've learned to feed it just enough to keep it quiet. Other people's pain. Other people's sacrifices. Other people's children.\n\nYou don't dream anymore. The flames have stopped. Elara's voice has faded. But something else lives in your sleep: a vast darkness, endless and cold. It speaks in a language you almost understand.\n\n'Not yet,' it whispers. 'But soon.'\n\nYou wander the roads, looking for something you'll never find. A purpose. A peace. An end.\n\nBut the void doesn't end. It just waits.\n\nAnd one day, when you've finally lost everything else, when there's nothing left to feed on but your own soul, it'll be waiting.\n\nThe Hollow Knight walks forever. And the void is his kingdom.",
    "ending": "HOLLOW",
    "choices": []
  },
  "VEX_CH1_DOCKS": {
    "id": "VEX_CH1_DOCKS",
    "character": "VEX",
    "description": "Rain hammers the cobblestones as you sprint through the Lower Docks, boots splashing through puddles. Three Guild enforcers are twenty paces behind, their shouts cutting through the thunder. You've stolen the Obsidian Ledger\u2014the names of every Guild member, every secret deal, every dirty coin. The Harbor Master's office burns behind you, casting flickering shadows across the alley walls.\n\nYou spot a narrow gap between two warehouses. The docks end in two directions: the public quay where City Watch patrols, or the private pier where fishing boats bob at anchor. Your heart pounds as you weigh your options, the ledger heavy in your coat.",
    "choices": [
