    "type": "story"
  },
  "VEX_CH4_DUEL": {
    "id": "VEX_CH4_DUEL",
    "character": "VEX",
    "description": "The Shadowmaster moves like smoke\u2014fast, impossibly fast. His blade whirls in patterns you've never seen, attacks from angles that shouldn't be possible. You parry, dodge, counter, but you're losing ground.\n\nA strike opens a gash along your ribs. Another catches your shoulder. Blood drips onto the ancient stone, and you realize you're fighting a losing battle.\n\nBut you've always been cleverer than your opponents. As the Shadowmaster presses his attack, you let yourself fall\u2014not backward, but to the side, toward the ceremonial dais. Your hand closes on a torch.\n\nFlame catches his cloak. He staggers, and you capitalize\u2014driving your blade up through his chin, into his brain.\n\nThe Shadowmaster falls. His guards freeze, unable to believe what they've seen. You stand over the body, bleeding but victorious.\n\nThe Guild is yours to command\u2014or destroy.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Claim the Guild's throne",
        "leads_to": "VEX_ENDING_SHADOWKING",
        "effects": {
          "dexterity": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Burn the Guild to the ground",
        "leads_to": "VEX_ENDING_LEGEND",
        "effects": {
          "dexterity": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Walk away from it all",
        "leads_to": "VEX_ENDING_WANDERER",
        "effects": {
          "dexterity": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ],
    "type": "story"
  },
  "VEX_ENDING_SHADOWKING": {
    "id": "VEX_ENDING_SHADOWKING",
    "character": "VEX",
    "description": "You sit upon the Shadowmaster's throne as the last of the resistance is crushed. The Guild survives\u2014stronger now, unified under your rule. You are the Shadow King, ruler of the city's underworld, master of shadows.\n\nIt wasn't the heroic path. You made deals with darkness and became it. But the Guild no longer preys on the innocent\u2014at least, not like before. You've imposed order on chaos, and the city breathes easier.\n\nIn your pocket, you carry the Obsidian Ledger. Your name is at the top now, written in ink that can never be erased. Some call you a monster. Others, a necessary evil. You call yourself... successful.\n\nThe shadows serve you now. And they will serve you forever.",
    "choices": [],
    "type": "story",
    "ending": "SHADOWKING"
  },
  "VEX_ENDING_LEGEND": {
    "id": "VEX_ENDING_LEGEND",
    "character": "VEX",
    "description": "The Guild burns. Every stronghold, every vault, every secret meeting place\u2014you've burned them all. The Obsidian Ledger is read aloud in the city square, and the names of the guilty are delivered to the courts. For the first time in a century, the Guild is broken.\n\nYou stand in the ashes of the Temple of Shadows, surrounded by cheering crowds who've come to see the end of an era. They call you hero. They sing songs of your bravery. Children will grow up in a city free from the Guild's terror, and they'll never know the nightmares you faced to give them that freedom.\n\nYour sister Lyra finds you in the aftermath. \"You did it,\" she whispers.\n\n\"We did it,\" you correct her.\n\nBut you know the truth. The shadows will always call to you. The question is whether you'll listen.",
    "choices": [],
    "type": "story",
    "ending": "LEGEND"
  },
  "VEX_ENDING_WANDERER": {
    "id": "VEX_ENDING_WANDERER",
    "character": "VEX",
    "description": "You leave the city behind. The Guild is weakened, perhaps broken\u2014Miravel and Corvus will finish what you started. You've done your part. Now it's time to disappear.\n\nOn the road out of the city, you meet a merchant caravan heading north. You join them as a guard, your sword arm earning your keep. No one knows your name here. No one knows what you've done.\n\nAt night, you stare at the stars and wonder if you made the right choice. The Guild still exists, somewhere in the shadows. But so do you\u2014free, alive, unbound.\n\nPerhaps that's enough. Perhaps it has to be.\n\nThe road stretches ahead, and you walk it one step at a time, leaving the past behind.",
    "choices": [],
    "type": "story",
    "ending": "WANDERER"
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_ESTATE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_ESTATE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Rain hammers against your hood as you stand in the shadow of what was your home.\n\nFive years. You count them in scars, in sleepless nights, in the cold calculation of revenge. The Vance Estate burns in your memory\u2014not with fire that night, but with something worse: the silence after the blades found your parents' throats.\n\nThe official report called it a carriage accident. Lord Castellan signed the investigation papers himself, wearing your father's signet ring. He inherited the company, the house, the name. Everything.\n\nBut he didn't inherit you.\n\nYou're not the child who hid in the carriage that night, watching your father die. You're something else now. Something with teeth.\n\nThree paths lie before you: the careful path of information, the bleeding path of immediate action, or the winding path of building alliances. You have five years of patience stored like poison in your veins.\n\nWhat do you do?",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Gather information first",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_GATHER",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Strike immediately",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE",
        "effects": {
          "strength": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Find allies in the shadows",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH1_ALLIES",
