        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_CULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_CULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "The Ashfield Cult meets in the burned Temple of Ash, three miles outside Thornwick.\n\nYou watch from the treeline as hooded figures gather in the moonlight. Their leader stands on the altar\u2014a woman in black, her face hidden. She speaks of the Hollow, the void that existed before creation. She speaks of the crown, seven pieces scattered, seven fragments of power.\n\nOne of them mentions Castellan. 'The merchant prince pays for our protection. He provides cover for our operations.'\n\nYou understand now. Your father found something\u2014a piece of the crown\u2014and tried to destroy it. That's why they killed him. That's why they killed your mother.\n\nThe Cult must never reunite the crown. Your parents understood that. Now you do too.\n\nYou'll need allies for what's coming.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Find the Circle of Mages",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK",
        "effects": {
          "intelligence": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
        "text": "Infiltrate as a initiate",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_INFILTRATE",
        "effects": {
          "stealth": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "C",
        "text": "Track Castellan's movements",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_CONFRONT",
        "effects": {
          "dexterity": 1
        },
        "requires": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "ELARA_CH1_VAULT": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_VAULT",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You spend two weeks mapping the estate's defenses. Twelve guards, rotating shifts. Wards on the vault\u2014a standard merchant's protection, nothing magical. Castellan cheats his taxes, not his security.\n\nBut you notice something: every third night, the guards change shifts at midnight. A five-minute window when the eastern wall is bare.\n\nYou also notice Castellan's habit: he visits the vault every week, alone. Never with guards. Whatever's inside, he wants to be the only one who sees it.\n\nThe piece of the crown calls to you. You've felt it since you were a child\u2014that strange pull toward things that shouldn't exist. Your parents told you it was a gift. Now you know better.\n\nIt's a curse. And it's the only thing that can buy you the power you need.",
    "choices": [
      {
        "letter": "A",
        "text": "Wait for the midnight window",
        "leads_to": "ELARA_CH2_NETWORK",
        "effects": {
          "stealth": 2
        },
        "requires": null
      },
      {
        "letter": "B",
