  "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH1_STRIKE",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "Night. Castellan's study. He's working late, as usual\u2014a\u8d2a\u5a6a man never rests.\n\nYou slip through the servant's entrance. The guards don't notice you; they never do. Your father's study is ahead, warm light spilling under the door. You can hear him muttering about shipments, about profits, about the Cult's latest demands.\n\nThen you hear your name.\n\n'The Vance girl is still out there,' someone says. Castellan. 'Find her. Finish what we started.'\n\nYour hand finds your blade. Five years of patience\u71c3\u70e7 in a single heartbeat.\n\nBut you hesitate. Killing him won't answer your question: why did they die? What did they find?\n\nYou pull back from the door. Not yet. You need more information.\n\nFor now.",
    "choices": [
