  "ELARA_CH2_MEETING": {
    "id": "ELARA_CH2_MEETING",
    "character": "ELARA",
    "description": "You arrange a meeting with Castellan, posing as a merchant seeking investment.\n\nHis study is exactly as you remember. He wears your father's chair like a trophy. His eyes scan you, calculating.\n\n'You have your father's eyes,' he says. 'The same eyes that saw too much.'\n\nYour heart freezes. But your face remains calm.\n\n'I represent eastern interests,' you say. 'We have... mutual friends. The Cult speaks highly of your operations.'\n\nHis face goes pale. Then smooth. 'You've come a long way to die, girl.'\n\nGuards appear at the door. But you've planned for this.\n\nYour network moves in the shadows. Marco's evidence reaches the queen's council. Servants you've bribed spread word of his crimes. And somewhere in the city, your allies are burning his warehouses.\n\n'You made a mistake,' you tell him. 'You should have finished the job five years ago.'\n\nThe siege begins.",
    "choices": [
